column1: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Human Kidney with CODEX

column2: Andrea J. Radtke; Christopher Werlein; Ellen M. Quardokus; Diane C. Saunders; Anna Martinez Casals; Presha Rajbhandari

column22: rationale

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure or cell type. It is expressed by NK cells and T cells and can be used to evaluate immune infiltration. This marker represents a prioritized target.

This marker defines major anatomical structures and cell types including proximal tubule cells, the descending limb of the loop of Henle, and glomerular capillary endothelial cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target.
This marker defines major anatomical structures and cell types including the collecting duct (principle cell). This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target.

This marker defines (but does not distinguish) diverse anatomical structures and cell types including proximal tubules, mesangial cells, fibroblasts, and activated endothelial cells. This marker represents a prioritized target.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure or cell type. It is broadly expressed by NK cells, T cells, B cells, plasma cells, and red blood cells. This marker can be used to evaluate immune infiltration and represents a prioritized target.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure or cell type. It can be used to evaluate proliferating cells and regenerating tubular cells. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines glomeruli and is expressed by glomerular podocytes and some endothelial cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure or cell type. It is broadly expressed by all hematopoietic cells and can be used to evaluate immune infiltration. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines epithelial cells of the thick ascending limb of Henle's loop and of the proximal part of the distal convoluted tubules. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target.
This marker defines major anatomical structures and cell types associated with the tubular epithelium. This marker represents a prioritized target.

This marker defines glomeruli, the kidney interstitium, and targets a marker highly expressed by podocytes, mesenchymal cells, fibroblasts, and mesangial cells. Vimentin and synaptopodin are useful markers for podocyte identification. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target.

This marker may be used to evaluate immune-mediated nephritis. Variable expression of this marker in glomeruli and tubules has been reported across individuals. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker broadly defines all blood endothelial cell subtypes in the kidney. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines peritubular capillary and glomerular endothelium. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines distal convoluted tubules, collecting ducts, and the loop of Henle. It is useful for segmentation. This marker represents a  prioritized target in the kidney OMAP.
This marker defines the basement membrane and is useful for segmentation. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the kidney OMAP.
This marker defines peritubular capillary and glomerular endothelium. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines major anatomical structures and cell types including the distal convoluted tubules, connecting segment, and cortical collecting duct. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure or cell type. It broadly defines the epithelial cells of the kidney. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker defines populations of stromal cells including smooth muscle cells and (myo)fibroblasts. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker specifically defines juxtaglomerular cells. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker is an essential marker for mast cells and can be used to evaluate immune infiltration. This marker represents a prioritized target.
This marker is specifically expressed by peritubular capillary endothelial cells and represents a prioritized target.
This antibody defines glomeruli and primarily labels glomerular podocytes. This marker represents a prioritized target.
